docker-shadowsocks

This Dockerfile builds an image with the Python implementation of shadowsocks. Based on Centos 6.6 image.

Quick Start

This image uses ENTRYPOINT to run the containers as an executable.

    docker run -d -p <local_port>:1080 -e PASSWORD=yourpass oddrationale/docker-shadowsocks

For more command line options, refer to the shadowsocks documentation https://github.com/shadowsocks/shadowsocks

